<rss xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" version="2.0"><channel><title>i3 FAQ - Individual question feed</title><link>https://faq.i3wm.org/questions/</link><description>Frequently asked questions and answers about the i3 window manager</description><atom:link href="http://faq.i3wm.org/feeds/question/2116/" rel="self"></atom:link><language>en</language><copyright>Copyright i3, 2012</copyright><lastBuildDate>Sun, 30 Jun 2013 14:27:38 +0000</lastBuildDate><item><title>Lock of the mouse cursor for a moment</title><link>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/2116/lock-of-the-mouse-cursor-for-a-moment/</link><description>Is there a way to lock (or even hide) the mouse cursor for a moment (so it won't move) and then restore it to normal work?

It would be perfect if it could be done simply with a shortcut.

I thought about it because there were several situations when I had some windows on the screen and an accidental mouse movement made the window I was typing in lose focus.

Or maybe there is another way to prevent an active window from losing focus?</description><pubDate>Sun, 30 Jun 2013 12:49:33 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/2116/lock-of-the-mouse-cursor-for-a-moment/</guid></item><item><title>Answer by V0id for &lt;p&gt;Is there a way to lock (or even hide) the mouse cursor for a moment (so it won't move) and then restore it to normal work?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It would be perfect if it could be done simply with a shortcut.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I thought about it because there were several situations when I had some windows on the screen and an accidental mouse movement made the window I was typing in lose focus.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Or maybe there is another way to prevent an active window from losing focus?&lt;/p&gt;
 </title><link>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/2116/lock-of-the-mouse-cursor-for-a-moment/?answer=2117#post-id-2117</link><description>You can try to put

    focus_follows_mouse no

in your i3 config. Focus changes will be done on mouse-click, not on mouse-over.

[http://i3wm.org/docs/userguide.html#_focus_follows_mouse](http://i3wm.org/docs/userguide.html#_focus_follows_mouse)</description><pubDate>Sun, 30 Jun 2013 13:14:39 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/2116/lock-of-the-mouse-cursor-for-a-moment/?answer=2117#post-id-2117</guid></item><item><title>Comment by smiszym for &lt;p&gt;You can try to put&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;focus_follows_mouse no
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;p&gt;in your i3 config. Focus changes will be done on mouse-click, not on mouse-over.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://i3wm.org/docs/userguide.html#_focus_follows_mouse"&gt;http://i3wm.org/docs/userguide.html#&lt;em&gt;focus&lt;/em&gt;follows_mouse&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
</title><link>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/2116/lock-of-the-mouse-cursor-for-a-moment/?comment=2119#comment-2119</link><description>Works, I think it'll be good :) Thanks</description><pubDate>Sun, 30 Jun 2013 14:27:38 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/2116/lock-of-the-mouse-cursor-for-a-moment/?comment=2119#comment-2119</guid></item></channel></rss>